Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 163, 14. Name Xenostratos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0187.19.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0665)
